             <img alt="" src="http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/8b3d681fc6760c2aaa8e6a24fd74ce5a?s=55&amp;d=identicon&amp;r=G" class="avatar avatar-55" height="55" width="55"> 
            </div>
            <!-- .comment-meta --> 
            <div class="comment-content"> 
             <p>How much stage time do undergraduates get at these schools? My experience tells me “very little”. How many sets or costumes designed by undergraduate students get actually constructed? My answer is the same. While they may crank out BA graduates, few are actually qualified to enter the field.</p> 
             <p id="comment-like-600" data-liked="comment-not-liked" class="comment-likes comment-not-liked"><a href="http://onstageblog.com/2015/02/19/the-best-b-a-in-theatre-programs-in-the-country-in-2015/?like_comment=600&amp;_wpnonce=0974cb2529" class="comment-like-link needs-login" rel="nofollow" data-blog="71050352"><span>Like</span></a><span id="comment-like-count-600" class="comment-like-feedback">Like</span></p> 
             <div class="reply"> 
              <a class="comment-reply-link" href="/2015/02/19/the-best-b-a-in-theatre-programs-in-the-country-in-2015/?replytocom=600#respond" onclick="return addComment.moveForm( &quot;comment-600&quot;, &quot;600&quot;, &quot;respond&quot;, &quot;1598&quot; )" aria-label="Reply to Gerry Blanchard">Reply</a> 
             </div>
             <!-- .reply --> 
            </div> 
