        <li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 highlander-comment" id="li-comment-609"> 
         <div id="comment-609" class="clear"> 
          <div class="comment-meta">
            Kirk Jackson 
           <div class="comment-date">
            February 21, 2015
           </div> 
           <img alt="" src="http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/a083e95f5888aeaef0b5be6c40f67a56?s=55&amp;d=identicon&amp;r=G" class="avatar avatar-55" height="55" width="55"> 
          </div>
          <!-- .comment-meta --> 
          <div class="comment-content"> 
           <p>Thank you for including Bennington College in your list of top BA theatre programs. Lacking a graduate program, all opportunities go to undergraduates. The majority of our productions are student designed and directed, and sometimes even written. Freshmen routinely are cast in main stage shows and we are too small an institution to ‘crank out’ any kind of graduate. Many alumni (and all the faculty) work professionally in television, film and theatre – writing, performing, producing, and designing. We are a small institution with a large impact and we like that way. Thanks for the recognition.</p> 
           <p id="comment-like-609" data-liked="comment-not-liked" class="comment-likes comment-not-liked"><a href="http://onstageblog.com/2015/02/19/the-best-b-a-in-theatre-programs-in-the-country-in-2015/?like_comment=609&amp;_wpnonce=86424ad481" class="comment-like-link needs-login" rel="nofollow" data-blog="71050352"><span>Like</span></a><span id="comment-like-count-609" class="comment-like-feedback">Liked by <a href="#" class="view-likers" data-like-count="1">1 person</a></span></p> 
