           <img alt="" src="http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/f7778ebdffbeab0f6b89ed2eb434e86f?s=55&amp;d=identicon&amp;r=G" class="avatar avatar-55" height="55" width="55"> 
          </div>
          <!-- .comment-meta --> 
          <div class="comment-content"> 
           <p>Not one Midwestern school? Give me a break.</p> 
           <p id="comment-like-853" data-liked="comment-not-liked" class="comment-likes comment-not-liked"><a href="http://onstageblog.com/2015/02/19/the-best-b-a-in-theatre-programs-in-the-country-in-2015/?like_comment=853&amp;_wpnonce=342e557a48" class="comment-like-link needs-login" rel="nofollow" data-blog="71050352"><span>Like</span></a><span id="comment-like-count-853" class="comment-like-feedback">Like</span></p> 
           <div class="reply"> 
            <a class="comment-reply-link" href="/2015/02/19/the-best-b-a-in-theatre-programs-in-the-country-in-2015/?replytocom=853#respond" onclick="return addComment.moveForm( &quot;comment-853&quot;, &quot;853&quot;, &quot;respond&quot;, &quot;1598&quot; )" aria-label="Reply to Jane Drake Brody">Reply</a> 
           </div>
           <!-- .reply --> 
          </div> 
         </div>
         <!-- #comment-853 --> </li>
        <!-- #comment-## --> 
        <li class="comment byuser comment-author-faraone2015 odd alt thread-even depth-1 highlander-comment" id="li-comment-899"> 
         <div id="comment-899" class="clear"> 
          <div class="comment-meta"> 
           <a href="http://faraonesite.wordpress.com" rel="external nofollow" class="url">faraone2015</a> 
           <div class="comment-date">
            March 1, 2015
           </div> 
           <img alt="" src="http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/c7077c2cdea310f4b00834bf962da798?s=55&amp;d=identicon&amp;r=G" class="avatar avatar-55" height="55" width="55"> 
          </div>
          <!-- .comment-meta --> 
          <div class="comment-content"> 
           <p>It was certainly a pleasure reading about my alma mater (CUA) and other schools whose work I know and respect, especially Wesleyan and Bennington, not to mention Emerson College, which my daughter attends. But before your next list appears, please take some time and travel further north in Vermont to Middlebury College. Our department has all of the things you indicate as important — three performing venues, a professionally active faculty and many performance opportunities (we have four faculty shows a year and between 8 and 12 student productions, 24 hour play festivals, newcomers’ shows and the like). Perhaps the most important difference is our NYC based professional theatre company, Potomac Theatre Project (PTP/NYC), now entering its 29th season. 10-12 undergraduates annually appear with the company, not as spear carriers, but in visible and significant roles opposite experienced professional actors. Much more information (including much about our distinguished alumni, active in every area of theatre, film and television). Please link through to <a href="http://potomactheatreproject.org/" rel="nofollow">http://potomactheatreproject.org/</a> and <a href="http://www.middlebury.edu/academics/thea" rel="nofollow">http://www.middlebury.edu/academics/thea</a>. Thanks!</p> 
           <p id="comment-like-899" data-liked="comment-not-liked" class="comment-likes comment-not-liked"><a href="http://onstageblog.com/2015/02/19/the-best-b-a-in-theatre-programs-in-the-country-in-2015/?like_comment=899&amp;_wpnonce=4bf957855d" class="comment-like-link needs-login" rel="nofollow" data-blog="71050352"><span>Like</span></a><span id="comment-like-count-899" class="comment-like-feedback">Like</span></p> 
